A

ApiFactory - Class in kr.co.elpusk.android.liblpu237
This class is a factory pattern implementation for creating instances based on the version of the ApiInterface.
Currently, only one version exists, so the getInstance() method only accepts the 'LAST' parameter.
If you want to use API of liblpu237, you have to create the instance of ApiInterface by ApiFactory.getInstance().
ApiFactory.VERSION - Interface in kr.co.elpusk.android.liblpu237
the definition of version string.
ApiInterface - Interface in kr.co.elpusk.android.liblpu237
All API class must be implement these interfaces.
API user have to use methods of this interface only.
Don't use a method of this interface implementer directly.

Open(String) - Method in interface kr.co.elpusk.android.liblpu237.ApiInterface

you must call SetupForRead() or ToolsMsrStartGetSetting() before using another method.
SetupForRead() read a minimum system parameter for reading msr or ibutton.
ToolsMsrStartGetSetting() read all most system parameter for changing system parameters.

Run(Lpu237Callback.Result, byte[], Lpu237Callback.TypeRx) - Method in class kr.co.elpusk.android.liblpu237.lpu237.Lpu237Callback
To use WaitMsrOriButtonWithCallback(), you need to extend this class and implement the Run() method.
The Run() method will be called when the reading is done.
Run(Lpu237Callback.Result, String) - Method in class kr.co.elpusk.android.liblpu237.lpu237.Lpu237DoneCallback
To use ToolsMsrStartApplySetting() or ToolsMsrSetInterfaceToDeviceAndApply(),
you need to extend this class and implement the Run() method.
The Run() method will be called when processing is done.
If the result is not Lpu237Callback.RESULT_SUCCESS,
it indicates an error has occurred or the operation was canceled by the user.
In such cases, the task can be retried or the API usage can be terminated.
because this method is called API internal thread, always be careful to avoid deadlock.
Run(Lpu237Callback.Result, String, int, int) - Method in class kr.co.elpusk.android.liblpu237.lpu237.Lpu237GetSetCallback
To use ToolsMsrStartGetSetting() or ToolsMsrStartSetSetting(),
you need to extend this class and implement the Run() method.
The Run() method will be repeatedly called until the reading and
writing of system parameters from the lpu237 are completed.
The user should program to wait until the initiated task is completely finished
when result is Lpu237Callback.RESULT_SUCCESS.
If the result is not Lpu237Callback.RESULT_SUCCESS,
it indicates an error has occurred or the operation was canceled by the user.
In such cases, the task can be retried or the API usage can be terminated.
because this method is called API internal thread, always be careful to avoid deadlock.
